    "content": "Libaan Ahmed Hassan, the presidential candidate for the Jubbaland State Party (JSP) coalition in Galmudug, delivered a major policy speech on July 18, 2026, in Dhusamareb. Addressing thousands of residents, he outlined his political agenda, focusing on two persistent obstacles that have hindered development in the region: the Al-Shabaab militant group and inter-clan conflicts.\n\nHassan, who received a warm welcome upon his arrival, emphasized that eliminating Al-Shabaab is a top priority. The group has maintained a presence in parts of Galmudug, carrying out attacks and disrupting daily life. He called for coordinated efforts with federal and regional security forces to dismantle the insurgency and restore stability.\n\nThe candidate also addressed the deep-rooted clan disputes that have sparked recurring violence, displacing families and undermining social cohesion. Hassan proposed a mediation framework involving traditional elders, civil society, and local authorities to resolve grievances and prevent future clashes.\n\nHis remarks come at a critical time as Galmudug prepares for leadership elections. The region has faced governance challenges amid security threats and political rivalries. For the Somali diaspora, these issues resonate as they affect family members remaining in the region and the potential for return and investment.\n\nRead the original report from Goobjoog here: https://goobjoog.com/2026/07/19/laba-caqabadood-oo-ragaadiyay-galmudug-oo-liibaan-axmed-xasan-ballanqaaday-inuu-xalinayo/",
